{
  "texts": [
    "By requiring that j = 1 2 for all of the physical state insertions, they satisfy Y 0 = 0 already.",
    "However, the Q(µ I) insertions are charged under Y 0 since[U 0, Q(µ I)] = -Q(µ I), [V 0, Q(µ I)] = Q(µ I),leading to a Y 0 charge of -2 for each Q insertion.",
    "We must cancel this by inserting (n + 2g -2) copies of the σ2 -spectrally flowed vacuum state W (u α) [7].",
    "We note in passing that it is natural to pair up one W (u α) with each of the (n + 2g -2) Q(µ I) and think of them as part of the measure.",
    "This means that a generic physical correlation function for the twisted sector ground states in the free field realisation is given byn-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i),where an integral over M g,n, with appropriate measure, is implicit."
  ]
}